Distribution. Described from Saint-Sever, southwestern France , Landes department. According to the Palearctic catalog, present in the following areas: Europe: Bosnia and Herzegovina , Czech Republic , France , Germany , Greece , Italy , Spain , Switzerland , “Caucasus”; North Africa: Morocco ; Asia: Israel , Syria , Turkey , Turkmenistan (
Jäch et al., 2006
). In addition, reported from the “Araks valley,” which could mean areas of Turkey , Armenia , Azerbaijan , and Iran , and from Khevsureti, i.e., “Kaukasus, Chewsurien” ( Georgia ) (
Berthélemy 1979
); Hungary (
Csabai, Sár 2007
), and Russia (Adygea) (
Nikitsky et al. 2010
).
